OL,4,Cquestions treatment, inquest hears
OL,6,FSebastian Naughton, the lawyer
OL,7,Frepresenting Mr Campbell's family,
OL,8,Fsaid the MRI's own investigation had
OL,9,Fidentified "some shortcomings" in
OL,10,Ftreatment, with reference to a delay
OL,11,Fin diagnosis during his final spell at
OL,12,Fthe MRI.
OL,14,FHe said the family, who were not
OL,15,Fpresent at the hearing at Manchester
OL,16,FCoroner's Court, wanted to know more
OL,17,Fabout his earlier stay at the MRI.
